The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Valley Ranch had a population of 128. The population density was {{convert|112.6|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Valley Ranch was 123 (96.1%) [[White Americans|White]], 2 (1.6%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 2 (1.6%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], and 1 (0.8%) from two or more races. No residents were [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]].<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Valley Ranch CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0681869 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 17, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 66 households, out of which 11 (16.7%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 38 (57.6%) were married-couple households, 3 (4.5%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 11 (16.7%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 14 (21.2%) had a male householder with no partner present. 20 households (30.3%) were one person, and 12 (18.2%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 1.94.<ref name=DP1/> There were 44 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (66.7% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Valley Ranch CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0681869 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 17, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 8 people (6.2%) under the age of 18, 1 people (0.8%) aged 18 to 24, 25 people (19.5%) aged 25 to 44, 26 people (20.3%) aged 45 to 64, and 68 people (53.1%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 65.5{{nbsp}}years. There were 62 males and 66 females.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 81 housing units at an average density of {{convert|71.2|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 66 (81.5%) were occupied. Of these, 59 (89.4%) were owner-occupied, and 7 (10.6%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

